# Build: Invite Accept Page (`app/(auth)/invite/page.js`)

## Context
Refer to CLAUDE.md for full project context, stack, folder structure, and Supabase client conventions before writing any code. This page lives inside the `(auth)` route group — no sidebar, no header, no dashboard chrome. Match the visual style of the login page exactly — same centered card layout, same Beem Hive wordmark at the top.

---

## What to build

The page a new customer lands on after clicking the invite link in their email. This is their very first experience of the Beem Hive platform — it needs to feel welcoming, clear, and fast.

The invite link Supabase sends looks like:
`https://beemhive.com/invite?token_hash=xxx&type=invite`

Next.js receives this as a page with query parameters. The token must be exchanged for a session before the customer can set their password.

This is a **Client Component** (`'use client'`).

---

## Page load sequence

On mount, before rendering the form, extract and verify the token from the URL:

```js
import { useSearchParams } from 'next/navigation'

const searchParams = useSearchParams()
const tokenHash = searchParams.get('token_hash')
const type = searchParams.get('type')
```

If `token_hash` is missing or `type` is not `'invite'` → render the **invalid link state** (see below) immediately, do not show the form.

If token is present → render the form. The token is exchanged with Supabase only when the customer submits their new password — not on page load.

