## Password strength indicator

A thin bar directly below the password field that updates in real time as the user types. Four levels:

| Level | Condition | Bar color | Label |
|---|---|---|---|
| Too short | < 8 characters | `rose-400` | "Too short" |
| Weak | ≥ 8 chars, only one character type | `amber-400` | "Weak" |
| Good | ≥ 8 chars, two character types | `blue-400` | "Good" |
| Strong | ≥ 10 chars, three or more character types (uppercase, lowercase, number, symbol) | `emerald-500` | "Strong" |

Character types: uppercase letters, lowercase letters, numbers, symbols (`!@#$%^&*` etc.).

The bar is a full-width track with a colored fill that animates width with `transition-all duration-300`. The label appears as small text to the right of the bar.

Minimum password requirement to allow submit: 8 characters. Show inline error below the field if they try to submit with fewer: "Password must be at least 8 characters."

---

## Validation (client-side, before Supabase call)

- Password: minimum 8 characters. Show error on blur or failed submit.
- Confirm password: must match password exactly. Show error message "Passwords don't match" inline below the confirm field — update in real time as they type the second field (don't wait for blur).

Do not show all errors upfront — only show a field's error after the user has touched it or after a failed submit attempt.

