## What NOT to do

- Do not exchange the token on page load — only on form submit
- Do not redirect to login after success — go directly to `/customer/profile`
- Do not show a generic "success" screen before redirecting — just redirect immediately
- Do not use `<form>` tags — use div + onClick handlers
- Do not skip the password strength indicator — it's the customer's first impression of product quality
- Do not show raw Supabase error messages — map to friendly strings
- Do not allow submit if passwords don't match — validate client-side before any Supabase call